<p>
  For these problems, you have two solutions.
  One is positive, and the other is negative.
  What do they mean?
</p>
<p>
  Take the ball from the end of its motion, and imagine that you play a tape backwards.
  The ball would go back up, come down, and go back into the person's hand.
  Imagine instead that the person and the cliff aren't even there.
  THe ball keeps traveling downward, and time moves backward, into <emph>negative time</emph>
  The ball would be at height zero at the time you indicated.
</p>

<p>
  What does negative time mean? It means that many seconds <emph>before</emph>
  the person threw the ball.
  Thus, if your answers are \( \Delta t= 5 \text{ s} \) and \( \Delta t= -3 \text{ s} \),
  that means that the ball reaches the ground 5 seconds after the person threw it,
  and it would have been at the ground 3 seconds <emph>before</emph> the person threw it.
</p>




